Comment: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Default,Fullmetal Alchemist,0000,0000,0000,,Brotherhood
Comment: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Default,Fullmetal Alchemist,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 34
Comment: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Default,Fullmetal Alchemist,0000,0000,0000,,===============================================================

Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.82,0:01:43.91,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,S-Superficial?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.49,0:01:45.91,Default,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, chilblains.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.47,0:01:49.33,Default,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,You were close to getting frostbite.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.03,0:01:53.26,Default,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,If you walk around in a blizzard for\Na long time with an automail like that,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.26,0:01:55.96,Default,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,you'll get frostbite where it is connected to your body.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.96,0:01:58.84,Default,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,You also won't be able to move very well unless you change your oil.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.41,0:02:02.47,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Is that Buccaneer guy's automail made differently?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.98,0:02:06.48,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,It's no good, Doc. I can't get this helmet off.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.68,0:02:08.74,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! That's my head!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.67,0:02:17.25,Default,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,All automail here must be made to be flexible, lightweight, and resistant to cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.82,0:02:24.74,Default,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,So through trial and error, an automail made with duralumin, carbon fiber, nickel, and copper was developed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.53,0:02:28.80,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it was just made of iron.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.80,0:02:31.11,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,No wonder I couldn't destroy it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.84,0:02:35.97,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,Hey Doc, you're not planning on spilling all the beans, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.97,0:02:37.26,Default,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,Why, what's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.54,0:02:40.11,Default,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,He's a famous State Alchemist.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.03,0:02:42.39,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure he's real?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.59,0:02:45.41,Default,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,He has the silver pocketwatch.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.99,0:02:49.21,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,A guy like this is of equal standing to a major?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.03,0:02:55.64,Default,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,If you're planning on staying up north for a while, you should switch to a cold climate automail.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.89,0:02:57.90,Default,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,Where does your automail mechanic work?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.43,0:03:00.32,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Rush Valley.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.20,0:03:04.83,Default,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,They knew a customer was heading up north and didn't even bother to tell you the dangers or offer a replacement?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.27,0:03:09.30,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Well... I didn't tell her that I was going to be up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.80,0:03:14.71,Default,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't want to die, you need to get it replaced;\Neven if it means your mechanic has to take a trip here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.17,0:03:17.44,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.44,0:03:19.23,Default,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,That'll be 100 cenz for the coffee.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.70,0:03:22.05,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,What a cheap trick...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.33,0:03:24.86,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,And this coffee tastes worse than the one at Eastern Headquarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.86,0:03:26.46,Default,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,Your fault for letting your guard down.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.82,0:03:31.99,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,So? What did you come here to do with that normal automail of yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.99,0:03:34.12,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,Coming along without even passing through Headquarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.12,0:03:35.44,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.44,0:03:39.50,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We came here with a letter of introduction to see if Major General Armstrong could help us out,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.50,0:03:44.41,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,but that general didn't even listen to me and was\Nblabbering on about how she'd pluck my antenna off...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.52,0:03:47.20,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Did you call, little brat?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.72,0:03:49.23,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,"L-Little"...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.23,0:03:50.03,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.03,0:03:51.73,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,If you've got something to say, just say it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.23,0:03:54.21,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,M-My hair...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.14,0:04:03.71,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I look ridiculous...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.26,0:04:14.86,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,So... I hear you're on good terms with my little brother, Alex.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.89,0:04:16.86,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Is he doing well?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.08,0:04:19.00,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.00,0:04:21.08,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,As muscular as always.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.08,0:04:22.61,Default,Both,0000,0000,0000,,He's as cheerful as can be.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.03,0:04:25.28,Default,Both,0000,0000,0000,,"Tch"?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.55,0:04:26.83,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Nevermind that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.83,0:04:30.79,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Moving right along, tell me why you came to see me without going through Headquarters first.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.10,0:04:34.58,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Don't forget to include why that armor is empty, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.53,0:04:40.00,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It's actually... something I don't want a lot of people to know about.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.30,0:04:42.17,Default,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,You've got nothing to worry about.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.17,0:04:44.67,Default,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,Most of the people here have circumstances of their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.67,0:04:48.01,Default,Doc,0000,0000,0000,,It's not uncommon for us to have things we don't want others to hear, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.47,0:04:53.09,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It's the kind of thing that could get me\Ncourt-martialed if people were to find out...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.09,0:04:55.48,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I've done things of that caliber, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.35,0:04:57.90,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Brother, listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.66,0:05:01.09,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think she'll forgive us unless we tell her something.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.09,0:05:03.36,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,But Winry is practically a hostage.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.79,0:05:04.82,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I have an idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.82,0:05:08.30,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Let's leave out the part about the\NFührer President and the Homunculi.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.30,0:05:09.72,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,What are you whispering on about?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.72,0:05:10.78,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have all day!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.38,0:05:15.16,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Then I guess we can just tell her,\N"We're on a journey to get our bodies back".
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.63,0:05:29.30,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So that's why you're looking for a girl who carries this cat around.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.21,0:05:32.22,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I get it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.58,0:05:34.04,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Then will you help us-
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.04,0:05:41.15,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I get you are scatterbrains who act without thinking and end up adding fuel to flames because of your carelessness.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.64,0:05:44.15,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to keep fools like you in my castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.15,0:05:49.16,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously... why don't the higher-ups at Central keep fools like you chained up?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.67,0:05:50.91,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Leave here at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.70,0:05:58.75,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,...is what I'd like to say, but I'm highly interested in Eastern Alchemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.75,0:06:02.67,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,You two are acquainted with that girl from Xing, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.93,0:06:04.67,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I guess you could say that...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.67,0:06:07.01,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,It's technology we don't have in this country.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.01,0:06:08.18,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I want it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.52,0:06:11.05,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,You can never have enough technology.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.05,0:06:15.18,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Especially in this land, where we frequently combat Drakma, a large nation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.47,0:06:19.44,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Depending on how we apply it, Eastern Alchemy may become a useful combat tool for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.44,0:06:20.69,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Hang on!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.03,0:06:24.16,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Eastern Alchemy is especially versed in medicinal purposes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.16,0:06:24.69,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Using that for war-
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.85,0:06:26.02,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Did I give you permission to speak?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.02,0:06:29.26,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,You're nothing but dogs that do nothing but bark within the borders of the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.75,0:06:35.49,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you forget for a second that you fools are living in peace because there exist those who protect the borders.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.95,0:06:38.34,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I am in charge of protecting the northern border.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.34,0:06:41.74,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,If the technique would be useful to my duty, then I'll take it. Whatever it may be.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.25,0:06:46.95,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Leave the search for the little girl to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.45,0:06:49.59,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want you two out of the fortress.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.45,0:06:52.91,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,And Major Miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.91,0:06:53.66,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Ma'am?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.66,0:06:55.10,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Give these two some work to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.10,0:06:55.89,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,W-What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.96,0:06:59.39,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,"If a man will not work, he shall not eat."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.31,0:07:02.03,Default,Both,0000,0000,0000,,Can't argue with that...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.66,0:07:06.90,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,They've got quite a rough history behind them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.12,0:07:13.41,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Although they seem to be fairly experienced in combat, I now know that they're just brats on the inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.70,0:07:14.91,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Also...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.57,0:07:19.41,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,It seems like they have some secrets they're not willing to share with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.11,0:07:30.74,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what are you going to make us do exactly?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.35,0:07:38.35,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,The doctor said that a lot of people here have\Ncircumstances of their own. Does that go for you, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.25,0:07:45.15,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,So you ask us about every detail of our lives,\Nand now you're ignoring us? Talk about unfair!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.92,0:07:49.15,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Do you really want to know?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.74,0:07:54.90,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Red eyes?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.90,0:07:55.91,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,An Ishbalan?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.38,0:07:57.54,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Why...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.54,0:08:02.34,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I heard that all of the soldiers of Ishbalan descent were purged before the extermination...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.32,0:08:07.01,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,I do have some Ishbalan blood in me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.01,0:08:11.62,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,However, my grandmother, my father, and my wife do not.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.99,0:08:17.05,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,The colors of my skin and eyes came from my grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.85,0:08:21.28,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Amestrian...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.72,0:08:25.33,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,You sure had your way with\Nthe land of my ancestors, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.72,0:08:40.08,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,You Ishbalans burned down my hometown, too, and even killed my friend's parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.26,0:08:41.58,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Cut it out, Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.49,0:08:53.67,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.18,0:08:57.55,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,You're actually the first one who talked back after I said that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.45,0:08:59.97,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,You were testing me, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.13,0:09:01.61,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,I apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.07,0:09:06.81,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,It's just that people view me with pity after that civil war.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.81,0:09:09.13,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,To be honest, I was getting sick of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.13,0:09:10.61,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,But you were different.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.59,0:09:19.12,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I've met Ishbalans who wanted to kill me, ones who tried to kidnap me, and others I've made peace with.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.77,0:09:22.31,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,So I've been through a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.94,0:09:29.37,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,And besides, I believe it's possible for individuals to be able to talk as equals without having to worry about race.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.60,0:09:43.01,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Were you enlisted in the military during the extermination, Major Miles?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.01,0:09:44.02,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.00,0:09:48.20,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,I served as assistant to Major General Armstrong then, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.10,0:09:51.92,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,The extermination began as soon as I was stationed here,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.28,0:09:56.30,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,and all of my Ishbalan relatives, beginning with my grandfather, were killed in the East.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.80,0:10:00.70,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,My life was saved due to my narrowly missing the requirements of the purge statute.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.25,0:10:03.70,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Did you not come to despise the military?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.91,0:10:06.71,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,You don't hesitate to ask anything, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.37,0:10:10.49,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I hate being ignorant.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.41,0:10:13.46,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I apologize if I offended you in any way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.37,0:10:17.38,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,A State Alchemist being ignorant, huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.86,0:10:24.26,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,I did despise what the military did.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.26,0:10:29.35,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,And at the same time, I had doubts about the\NMajor General for keeping me as her assistant.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.21,0:10:36.28,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,By having someone like me, a person with Ishbalan blood around, it could cause trouble with the soldiers here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.52,0:10:41.76,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Yet, the Major General didn't exile me,\Nso I turned on her in anger and demanded answers.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.58,0:10:47.54,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Briggs shall not fall, no matter what happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.31,0:10:54.02,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Every soldier here must be strong and flexible, fulfilling my every command.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.02,0:10:58.54,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,They must make up a sturdy army that would keep calm under all circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.16,0:11:02.89,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, there's no time for racism.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.73,0:11:12.27,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,{\fscx94}Because the blood of many races runs through your veins,\Nyou view this country from many angles and with many values.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.63,0:11:18.84,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,{\fscx99}Because I was born and raised an Amestrian, I need someone like you by my side for me to be able to stand at the top.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.84,0:11:22.58,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Follow my command without complaint, Miles!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.33,0:11:25.32,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Perfectly logical.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.32,0:11:27.54,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Not to mention that her words carried no deception.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.39,0:11:35.19,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,I proceeded to ask her, "Even then, what if the Ishbalan in me couldn't forgive the army and took over my mind?"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.64,0:11:37.55,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,How do you think she responded to that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.55,0:11:39.80,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Very well. Bring it on.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.80,0:11:43.05,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I'll accept a duel from you at any time, as a representative of the army.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.27,0:11:44.48,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Is what she said.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.48,0:11:46.36,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,What an evil woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.36,0:11:48.56,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It should be easy saying that with a battalion at her back.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.56,0:11:50.56,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm fairly certain...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.56,0:11:52.71,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I'll slice you up in a one-on-one duel!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.71,0:11:54.48,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,...her eyes were saying that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.98,0:12:02.89,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Are you aware of the universal law at this base?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.89,0:12:05.07,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,"Survival of the fittest", was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.26,0:12:06.34,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.34,0:12:10.07,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Ones without power will die,\Nand ones with power will survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.07,0:12:14.39,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,This is always true, under any circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.39,0:12:15.83,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,It's very simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.07,0:12:21.26,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,There are no underlings, bosses, and no distinctions between race, ethnicities, and gender.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.43,0:12:28.50,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,There's a good example of the survival of the fittest concept.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.50,0:12:30.93,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,You lived through it because you had good luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.16,0:12:35.83,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like the guys who were supposed to be removing the icicles loafed on the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.24,0:12:37.83,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,It's your job now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.20,0:12:41.32,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,I'll tell one of my men to give you\Na tour of the inside once you finish.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.74,0:12:47.68,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I can't reach that high!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.68,0:12:49.30,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Don't tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.65,0:12:53.06,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Warrant Officer Falman!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.06,0:12:54.58,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,Elric Brothers!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.58,0:12:56.27,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.27,0:12:59.67,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Speak for yourself! I thought you were getting transferred to Northern Headquarters!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.91,0:13:04.17,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,I was actually sent here from Northern Headquarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.45,0:13:06.21,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,You were promoted to Second Lieutenant!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.21,0:13:07.18,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.37,0:13:09.90,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Oh. Congratulations on your promot-
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.90,0:13:12.32,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,But why are you in charge of the icicles?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.32,0:13:15.79,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,If you're here working the duties of the enlisted...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.93,0:13:19.69,Default,Both,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like that'll be your last promotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.88,0:13:21.57,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.35,0:13:27.05,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,This is the development lair.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.10,0:13:28.95,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, what's {\i1}that{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.60,0:13:36.46,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,They're developing weapons using the best technology in the country under orders from Major General Armstrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.12,0:13:39.13,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Even automails for combat?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.13,0:13:39.76,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.76,0:13:40.88,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,Let me show you something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.12,0:13:52.81,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,This is the lowest level of Briggs.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.55,0:13:55.13,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It's really warm down here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.13,0:13:56.56,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Totally different from how it is up at the top.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.18,0:14:00.16,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,The lifeline of the fortress is gathered here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.16,0:14:04.68,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,Even if the top of the fortress is attacked,\Nthe central part underground will remain unscathed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.57,0:14:08.28,Default,Bobby,0000,0000,0000,,Out of my way!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.54,0:14:10.31,Default,Bobby,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be milling around!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.95,0:14:11.66,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.66,0:14:13.91,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Hey Bobby, this way!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.91,0:14:15.11,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,It's this pipe.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.15,0:14:22.17,Default,Bobby,0000,0000,0000,,This sound...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.37,0:14:26.61,Default,Bobby,0000,0000,0000,,It's coming from underground.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.61,0:14:26.92,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.11,0:14:30.68,Default,Bobby,0000,0000,0000,,It sounds like... someone's digging.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.17,0:14:35.10,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me the Drakmans are building\Nan underground passage beneath the fortress?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.10,0:14:37.26,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,It's really close!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.61,0:14:39.81,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,What a drag...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.32,0:14:42.43,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,Really, what a drag...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.90,0:14:46.04,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,It's such a drag, I could die.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.89,0:14:50.20,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,But dying is also a drag.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.90,0:15:12.80,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Solf J. Kimblee?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.25,0:15:19.15,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,He was badly injured on a freight train on the way here and was hospitalized at the foot of the mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.15,0:15:21.81,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,He requests that Briggs supports him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.27,0:15:25.70,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Wasn't the Crimson Alchemist serving in jail?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.13,0:15:29.82,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, he was discharged.\NUnder orders from the Führer President.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.39,0:15:31.77,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I don't like the sound of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.06,0:15:35.30,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.30,0:15:37.33,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Intruders, ma'am! From underground!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.63,0:15:39.00,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.01,0:15:56.39,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Homunculus!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.42,0:16:00.71,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.71,0:16:05.90,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,So they knew we came up here to search for ways to fight against the Homunculi?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.72,0:16:19.54,Default,Both,0000,0000,0000,,Don't fall asleep!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.35,0:16:23.75,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.75,0:16:25.82,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.82,0:16:29.00,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,You heard about us from your Father at Central, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.00,0:16:30.56,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.56,0:16:34.76,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,We just came here to search for ways to get our bodies back...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.76,0:16:36.93,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,Who... are you guys?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.89,0:16:41.15,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,I... have to dig.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.15,0:16:43.12,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,What a drag...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.12,0:16:45.44,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,Such a drag...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.03,0:16:48.21,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, could it be that he...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.21,0:16:52.94,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Maybe neither Father nor the\NFührer President have told him about us yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.45,0:17:00.03,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,You bastard! So you {\i1}are{\i0\fscx30} {\r} spies from Drakma!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.03,0:17:01.69,Default,Both,0000,0000,0000,,We're not!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.69,0:17:04.54,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,Then why are you speaking to the intruder like you're friends?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.54,0:17:06.40,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We're not friends!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.40,0:17:07.43,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,You can't trick me!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.43,0:17:08.56,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,This is in the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.56,0:17:10.29,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We're not lying!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.29,0:17:11.09,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We're just...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.95,0:17:21.56,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,There's... so much room here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.90,0:17:23.98,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,Where am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.20,0:17:29.40,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,Do I not have to dig anymore?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.40,0:17:30.60,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.93,0:17:36.78,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,Bullets are ineffective?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.86,0:17:42.45,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,Where... am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.67,0:17:51.24,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,This is bad! He's headed for the development lair!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.24,0:17:51.96,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,After him!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.12,0:17:53.35,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,Contact the men up there!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.35,0:17:54.59,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We need to go after him, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.59,0:17:55.41,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.26,0:18:23.28,Default,Man,0000,0000,0000,,He's huge...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.88,0:18:27.91,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,It's... warm in here...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.24,0:18:29.08,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Stay where you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.03,0:18:38.88,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Put out the fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.88,0:18:39.77,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.45,0:18:52.11,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I know I hit him...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.20,0:18:54.23,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,It's no use, Boss!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.23,0:18:56.55,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,Bullets don't work against him!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.55,0:18:57.65,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.44,0:19:00.54,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,All noncombatants are to withdraw immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.95,0:19:02.07,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Shut off the alarm, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.62,0:19:05.47,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let Drakma know about this commotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.96,0:19:07.71,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I've brought it, Boss!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.79,0:19:10.68,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Has it been tested?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.10,0:19:12.84,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,There's no need for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.28,0:19:15.46,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,It's the proud of work of us developers!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.67,0:19:17.64,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Remove the fuse from the shell!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.64,0:19:18.76,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Aye, ma'am!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.89,0:19:30.89,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,First shell, loaded!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.09,0:19:32.23,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.52,0:19:35.73,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Bull's eye!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.93,0:19:45.74,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,Oww...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.50,0:19:53.79,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,It's a drag to feel pain, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.15,0:19:58.39,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Don't just sit there!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.39,0:19:59.13,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Load the next shell!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.57,0:20:03.38,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.78,0:20:18.86,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,Oww...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.09,0:20:22.86,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,Oh yeah, I forgot about my job.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.27,0:20:26.78,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,I have to dig.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.87,0:20:48.33,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It's no use, General!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.33,0:20:50.22,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,He won't die no matter what!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.45,0:20:51.68,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Won't die?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.29,0:20:54.00,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.00,0:20:56.19,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you know so much about that thing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.77,0:20:59.19,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I-I...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.21,0:21:01.93,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I don't like dilly-dalliers!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.93,0:21:04.81,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Answer everything that you {\i1}can{\i0\fscx30} {\r} answer!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.81,0:21:07.73,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,How do you know about that thing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.73,0:21:09.16,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Are you a spy from Drakma?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.35,0:21:10.33,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.56,0:21:12.47,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Then is that thing a spy?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.47,0:21:14.14,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.14,0:21:16.01,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Does that thing know you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.01,0:21:17.76,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Probably not.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.76,0:21:19.84,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,What {\i1}is{\i0\fscx30} {\r} that thing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.84,0:21:23.46,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I can't answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.46,0:21:25.51,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Who is commanding him to act?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.67,0:21:26.97,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I can't answer!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.01,0:21:29.47,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,And why can't you answer?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.31,0:21:32.97,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Please try to realize...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.98,0:21:38.70,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,This is my last question.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.70,0:21:41.23,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Do you two plan to ally yourselves with us?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.82,0:21:44.44,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to see the people here die.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.59,0:21:48.24,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me what his body is made of.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.03,0:21:53.24,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fairly certain his body structure and composition are identical to humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.98,0:21:55.79,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Identical to humans, huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.48,0:22:00.83,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Buccaneer, bring me some tank fuel.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.83,0:22:02.02,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to pour it on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.02,0:22:02.70,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.70,0:22:04.35,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I'm telling you, it's useless!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.35,0:22:06.22,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you light him on fire, he won't...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.49,0:22:09.47,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,I've already gathered from the\Nprevious attacks that he won't die.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.90,0:22:12.35,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, I'll just shut off his bodily functions.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.97,0:22:15.22,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,I'll let him have something far worse than flames.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.28,0:22:22.56,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,I'll show you how we do things at Briggs.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.06,0:23:59.87,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,The bodies that clash against each other..
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.87,0:24:01.71,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,The shells that explode in the air...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.95,0:24:06.23,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,{\fscx90}The battle against the Homunculus threatening the North defense.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.23,0:24:10.55,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Will it be us who will win the battle? Or perhaps...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.37,0:24:15.34,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, Fullmetal Alchemist:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.34,0:24:18.99,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 35, The Shape of This Country.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.96,0:24:21.93,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,All that stands in our way shall be annihilated.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.57,0:24:24.75,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,That is the law of the North.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.75,0:24:26.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
